			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Right, ADC #immediate adds two ~1.79 MHz clocks to the total execution time. Just now I coded up 115.2kbps serial and it's working well on a 6KB random test data set. I found that using 2 stop bits gives a little more breathing room in the receive code. The 57.6kbps routines I've been using have been reliable for a couple of years now, and the loader that uses them does a checksum verification after every complete transfer. I'd like to help if you're going to make a serial-based devcart. I'm really happy with mine.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

