				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Can one be made with a USB to serial adapter chip? Such chips are likely to run at 5V (just like USB itself) and thus not need a level shifter. With the 9-pin RS232 being eliminated from newer mainboards (and already gone from Macs for a decade), this might be important in the future.</div>

